\delta_\epsilon(x) = \begin{cases} 0&x<-\epsilon\\ 1/2\epsilon & -\epsilon\le x\le\epsilon\\0 & x\gt-\epsilon\end{cases}
\delta(x) = \delta_{\epsilon\rightarrow0}(x)
\delta(x) = \begin{cases} \infty & x=0 \\ 1 & x\neq0 \end{cases}
\int_{-\alpha}^\beta \delta(x)dx=1 \;\; \alpha\gt0, \; \beta\gt 0
